Mycoplasma pneumoniae infection in childhood respiratory pathology. Respiratory, extrarespiratory manifestations and immunological findings. A 2-year study. "Mycoplasma pneumoniae" respiratory infection was diagnosed by completed fixation assay in 81 ages 8 months to 14 years. Seventy had pneumonia and ten had bronchitis. The "Mycoplasma pneumoniae" represented the 25% of all pneumonia of any aetiology. Seventy per cent of cases occurred during spring and summer months. Rashes developed in 13 (16%) patients (maculo-papular, 6 Stevents-Johnson, 2